  <a href="#1" id="1">
   According to the State Flood Control and Drought Relief Headquarters,
  </a>
  <a href="#2" id="2">
   water levels of the Xi Jiang, Bei Jiang, Xiang Jiang, and Gan Jiang rivers are dropping.
  </a>
  <a href="#3" id="3">
   The Xi Jiang and Bei Jiang, in Guangdong Province,
  </a>
  <a href="#4" id="4">
   crested yesterday, the Bei Jiang at a record 10.39 meters.
  </a>
  <a href="#5" id="5">
   The industrialized Zhujiang Delta, however, is still threatened
  </a>
  <a href="#6" id="6">
   because it is traversed by a merged Xi Jiang and Bei Jiang.
  </a>
  <a href="#7" id="7">
   The Xiang Jiang crested on 19 June,
  </a>
  <a href="#8" id="8">
   but today the water level is still at 25 meters.
  </a>
  <a href="#9" id="9">
   Dike reinforcement, therefore, must be accelerated.
  </a>
  <a href="#10" id="10">
   The flood peak in Gan Jiang entered Boyang Lake on 20 June.
  </a>
